    <body><div type="letter">
      <p>Fordhook 1/2 pst 12 o'clock Tuesdy</p>
      <p>Dearest Mate. The enclosed from the Hen will be perfectly satisfactory to you, as it is to me, and I hope ou will allow the avis to stay as long as possible with her affectionate Hen.--</p>
      <p>Miss Murray is probably coming this evening, for one night only.-- I think I</p>
      <p>shall not go into Town today, as there is a most horrible wind, &amp; I have a return of sore throat-- very slight however.</p>
      <p>The ground was covered with this morning.-- The bright avis left her mateless nest at 1/2 pst 7 as usual, and thinks herself a particularly nice bird.--</p>
      <p>The young has had a very bad night, &amp; is not quite right today, but these variations must be expected during teething.--</p>
      <p>The report of Sophia (the thief) being very ill, is an entire mistake, as Potich ascertained yesterday. I am sorry to say it appears she has taken linen. At least some is missing unaccountably.</p>
      <p>I was so beyond measure weary by nine o'clock last night, that I could not help thinking how unfit I should be for Lady Philips's dinner.--</p>
      <p>Ou very nice nesting Avis A. A. K.</p>
